  "commentary": "With SPX at 6595.1 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-33.9B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+29.3B), dealers are currently in buy mode as they're short gamma below spot and will aggressively purchase any dip toward 6590/6580. The breakout regime with massive negative GEX (-57.8B) means dealers will amplify moves in both directions - they'll keep buying weakness toward 6590 but flip to selling pressure if we break above 6605. Watch the 6590-6605 corridor closely as it represents the immediate battleground between amplifying and stabilizing forces, with the gex_surge event suggesting heightened sensitivity to these levels.\n\nBottom line: expect big moves as dealers push price away from the current 6590-6605 zone.",
